e60::a 3. Use of subcontractor/sub-processor ::e
e61::a "3.1. The Processor shall not engage another supplier for the processing of the personal data, [sub-processor], without prior specific or general written authorisation of the Controller, and the sub-processor has confirmed that it undertakes to implement appropriate technical and organizational measures in such a manner that processing will meet the requirements of the Personal Data Regulation and this Terms and ensure the protection of the rights of the data subject." ::e
e62::a 3.1. This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue in full force and effect unless terminated.This Agreement may be terminated by either party’s prior written notice with a termination term of 60 days. ::e
e63::a 3.2. Any approved sub-processors are included in the Appendix to this Data Processing Terms. ::e
e64::a "3.2. The Company may terminate this Agreement without any prior notice and without being obliged to pay any sum as would have been payable to the Consultant, if the Consultant committed at any time any act of fraud, embezzlement, disparagement, or misappropriation against the Company." ::e
e65::a 3.3. Both Parties are entitled to cancel the Agreement with immediate effect in case of material breach of the contract. ::e
e66::a 3.3. The Controller has given the Processor a general written authorisation for the use of sub-processors for processing personal data under the Data Processing Terms. ::e
e67::a "3.4. Any sub-processor shall be imposed the same obligations as the Processor set forth in the Data Processing Terms in a written, binding agreement where in particular the sub-processor is providing sufficient guarantees to implement appropriate technical and organizational measures in such a manner that the processing will meet the requirements of the Personal Data Regulation and this Terms." ::e
e68::a "3.4. Should this Agreement be terminated, Consultant shall return to the Company any and all equipment, [including software accounts], and confidential information made available to it, if applicable, by the Company in order to provide the Services according to the Company's instructions." ::e
