e99::a 7. LIABILITY ::e
e100::a "7.1. For non-fulfilment or improper fulfillment of own liabilities under this Agreement, the responsible Party will compensate another Party caused and documentary approved damages to the fullest extent with the maximum possible compensation in the amount, paid or owed upon the Agreement regardless of the execution of the obligations under this Agreement and/or the elimination of violations." ::e
e101::a 7.2. Irrespective of the preceding paragraph liability shall be governed by the relevant provisions of the Norwegian Civil Code. ::e
e102::a 8. NON-SOLICITATION AND NON-COMPETE ::e
e103::a "8.1. The Consultant will not, for the duration of this Agreement and thereafter for a period of 6 months commencing on the date upon which the Agreement ceases, be concerned or participate in, whether as a consultant, employee in any other capacity, any business which directly compete or will compete with the Company’s software for hosting and management of online, [virtual], events." ::e
e104::a "8.2. The Consultant agrees that during the term of this Agreement and for 12 months after its termination, he/she shall not, directly or indirectly, induce or attempt to induce any customer, supplier, Company, licensee, or business relation of the Company to cease doing business with Company, or in any way harmfully interfere with the relationship between any customer, supplier, Company, licensee, and the Company." ::e
e105::a "8.3. The Consultant will not, for the duration of this Agreement and for 12 months thereafter, directly or indirectly on its own account or on behalf of or in conjunction with any person, approach any employees or consultants of the Company with a view to inducing such persons to terminate their employment or consulting relationship with the Company." ::e
e106::a 8.4. The Consultant acknowledges and agrees that the fee paid under this Agreement is sufficient enough for effectiveness and applicability of this clause. ::e
e107::a "8.5. The Consultant shall be free to take employment with or to be engaged as a consultant in any other company provided that such engagement or employment does not constitute a breach of this clause of this Agreement, or in any way prevents or detracts from the fulfillment of the Consultant's obligations according to this Agreement." ::e
e108::a "8.6. In the event of breach of the Consultant's duties regulated in this Clause, the Company may demand that the breach be discontinued and may claim liquidated damages from the Consultant." ::e
